commText: Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. Ishant will open the attack
250 or more IPL appearances 263 - MS Dhoni 256 - Rohit Sharma 255 - Dinesh Karthik 250 - Virat Kohli I0$
Ishant to Kohli, no run, sharp inswinger first up from Ishant. Bends in sharply off a good length to finish on off stump, Kohli gets forward to defend and is hit on the splice
Ishant to Kohli, 1 run, back of a length on off, sharp inswinger, Kohli presses forward, the ball climbs on him and he manages to steer it wide of short third. Again it struck him on the splice
Ishant to du Plessis, 1 run, good length outside off, another inswinger, and Faf guides it to deep backward point
Ishant to Kohli, no run, 136.7kph, back of a length outside off, Kohli gives the charge and looks to slap it through the off-side. But it kicks up sharply and beats the bat

Ishant to Kohli, 2 runs, back of a length on off, swinging back in, Kohli looks to punch hard from the crease and drags it off the inside half through midwicket. Fielder chases it down but Kohli comes charging back for two
Ishant to Kohli, SIX, Kohli climbs into this one! Short of length delivery swinging back in at the body, sits up above the waist and he nails the pull over midwicket
Khaleel Ahmed, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to du Plessis, no run, back of a length delivery just outside off, Faf hangs back and punches to cover

Khaleel Ahmed to du Plessis, FOUR, back of a length outside off, width on offer for Faf and he slaps it away through cover. Previous one had a hint of inswing, but this one was angling away, and he had the room to free his arms
Khaleel Ahmed to du Plessis, leg byes, 1 run, length ball down leg, and Faf misses out as he's struck on the thigh pad
Khaleel Ahmed to Kohli, 1 run, length ball across off, Kohli opens the face and steers it to deep backward point
Khaleel Ahmed to du Plessis, 1 run, sharp inswinger on leg stump and Faf is hit on the back pad. But there might've been an inside edge involved. It was comfortably missing leg stump as well

Khaleel Ahmed to Kohli, SIX, wow! If you didn't know how well Kohli has been timing it of late, just look at this. Full outside off, angling away, and he lofts it beautifully through the line over mid-off. Just an extension of the off-drive and it goes all the way
Mukesh Kumar, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to du Plessis, no run, beaten outside off
Mukesh Kumar to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mukesh Kumar to du Plessis, out Caught by Fraser-McGurk!! Second time in two games that Faf is caught at deep backward point. Full outside off, swinging away, he looks to loft it over cover but gets a thick outside edge. No mistake in the deep from Fraser-McGurk. du Plessis c Fraser-McGurk b Mukesh Kumar 6(7) [4s-1]
Will Jacks, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Will Jacks, 1 run, short of length outside off, Jacks punches it to deep backward point
Mukesh Kumar to Kohli, no run, good length on middle, slanted in, and Kohli gets an inside edge onto pad as he looks to drive
Mukesh Kumar to Kohli, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, doesn't give room to Kohli as he advances. He tries to free the arms but can only drag it off the inside half behind square
Mukesh Kumar to Will Jacks, no run, short of length on off, blocked down the pitch
Ishant Sharma [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack

Ishant to Kohli, FOUR, edged but well wide of the keeper! Back of a length outside off, Kohli stays in the crease and looks to punch through cover but it flies off a thick edge. Kohli and Ishant exchange a few words

Ishant to Kohli, SIX, pretty sure Ishant won't have much to say after this. Absolutely dismissive from Kohli. Fuller than a length on off, he maintains a solid base in the crease and whacks it a long way over wide long-on, running his wrists through the ball beautifully. Gosh he's in such good touch
Ishant to Kohli, no run, back of a length outside off, Kohli looks to dab it fine but is beaten
Ishant to Kohli, wide, back of a length delivery down leg, Kohli misses and it's called wide
Ishant to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Ishant to Kohli, out Caught by Abishek Porel!! Ishant has the last laugh and he's letting Kohli know about it. Kohli takes it sportingly as well. Fuller than a length outside off, he looks to drive without moving his feet, just throws his hands at it in ungainly fashion. But the ball kicks up and takes a healthy edge through to Porel. Both openers gone in successive overs. Kohli c Abishek Porel b Ishant 27(13) [4s-1 6s-3]
Rajat Patidar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Ishant to Rajat Patidar, no run, good length on off, defended
Ishant to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, short of length into the body, Patidar gets on his toes and tucks it into the on-side
Virat Kohli vs Ishant Sharma in the IPL Inns: 11 Runs: 112 Balls: 76 Dismissal: 1 SR: 147.36 4s/6s: 12/5
Mukesh Kumar to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, sublime timing! Fuller than a length outside off, he gets forward and creams it through extra cover. Lovely punch off the middle of the bat
Mukesh Kumar to Rajat Patidar, no run, back of a length on off, kicks up a touch and pops up off the splice. It falls well short of cover-point
Mukesh Kumar to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, back of a length on off, Patidar goes for a fierce pull but it goes high off a thick top-edge. Keeper runs back but it falls well behind him

Mukesh Kumar to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, another one creamed through extra cover! The ball is swinging and Mukesh pitches it up in search of that movement. But Patidar is equal to it as he unleashes another glorious drive. This one's in the air but in the gap
Mukesh Kumar to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, back of a length on off, sits up around the waist and Patidar finds the boundary again as he pulls it over midwicket
Mukesh Kumar to Rajat Patidar, no run, pushed to cover
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Axar to Will Jacks, no run, length ball sliding in on middle, Jacks defends down the pitch
Axar to Will Jacks, 1 run, length ball sliding in on middle, Jacks gets forward and punches it to long-off
Axar to Rajat Patidar, no run, length ball sliding down leg, Patidar tries clipping it away but it goes to short fine
Axar to Rajat Patidar, SIX, bit more air from Axar as he tosses it up on off, and Patidar capitalises! He stretches forward, reaches out and tonks it over wide long-on
Axar to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, back to a flatter trajectory. Length ball darted in on leg, 98kph, and Patidar works it through midwicket
Axar to Will Jacks, 2 runs, flat on leg stump, Jacks makes room to go over the off-side but miscues it over extra cover. He gets back for two as long-off cuts it off

Highlights (Overs 1-6) - Kohli hits Ishant for a six in the opening over - Khaleel concedes 13 off the 2nd over - Mukesh Kumar gets Faf with his second ball - Ishant has the last laugh as he gets rid of Kohli in his 2nd over - Patidar hits Mukesh for 3 fours as RCB take 14 off the 5th over - Axar ends the powerplay with a 10-run over
Kuldeep Yadav, comes into the attack

Kuldeep Yadav to Rajat Patidar, no run, Kuldeep gives this one a rip! Length ball drifting across off stump before turning in. Patidar is cramped going for the cut and chops it off a thick under-edge onto pad

Kuldeep Yadav to Rajat Patidar, SIX, way too full this time and it disappears! Tossed up on middle and leg, lands right in the slot and Patidar launches it straight down the ground. He's off to a flier
Kuldeep Yadav to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, flat on leg stump, Patidar tucks it through midwicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Will Jacks, SIX, again Kuldeep tosses it up and again he gets hammered! Too full on off stump, Jacks gets forward and clobbers it over long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Will Jacks, 1 run, googly on leg stump, length ball, Jacks hangs back and punches it to long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, tossed up on middle, Patidar knocks it through midwicket
Axar to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, flat length ball just outside off, hint of turn, Patidar hangs back and steers it to short third
Axar to Will Jacks, 1 run, 98kph length ball fired in on off, Jacks punches it to sweeper cover
Axar to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, flat on middle, back of a length, Patidar hangs back and tucks it to long-on
Axar to Will Jacks, 1 run, length ball outside off, Jacks punches it to long-off

Axar to Rajat Patidar, SIX, he has been so good against spin. This isn't all that short. Maybe just back of a length as Axar fires it in on middle, and Patidar is so quick to rock back in the crease as he pulls it over midwicket
Axar to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, flat outside off, Patidar cuts to deep point
Kuldeep Yadav to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 114.4kph back of a length on middle and leg, Patidar hangs back and tucks it through midwicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Will Jacks, SIX, whenever he's tossed it up, he's gone the distance. Third six off Kuldeep. Tossed up on off, Jacks reaches out and smashes the slog-sweep over midwicket

Kuldeep Yadav to Will Jacks, 1 run, oh he foxes him with the googly this time, but the catch is put down! Tossed up on leg stump, Jacks gets a thick top-edge as he goes for the slog-sweep and it goes high in the air. Goes behind the bowler, Axar runs back, doesn't get into a good position and barely even gets a hand
Kuldeep Yadav to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, swept hard wide of long-on and comes back for two
Kuldeep Yadav to Rajat Patidar, wide, well wide outside off, left alone

Kuldeep Yadav to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, dropped again! This was a comfortable catch and should've been gobbled at long-on. Darted in on middle, back of a length, Patidar is late on the pull and miscues it in the air. Hope runs in at long-on, gets to it easily but fails to hold on
Kuldeep Yadav to Will Jacks, no run, googly on off, pushed through flat, and beats Jacks on the outside edge as he's caught on the crease

Timeout! RCB going at a good clip, helped by some poor catching from DC. Both Jacks and Patidar got a life in the previous over. The pitch has had some spongy bounce but the ball is mostly coming on well
Khaleel Ahmed [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, thick top-edge on the pull from Patidar but it goes over the keeper. Back of a length delivery, he looks to take it on but it kicks up on him
Khaleel Ahmed to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, punched off the back foot to cover where a misfield allows them to take a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Will Jacks, FOUR, back of a length on off, Jacks makes room and slaps it over extra cover. It was perhaps a cutter from Khaleel. Jacks got hold of it nicely

Khaleel Ahmed to Will Jacks, 2 runs, again a chance goes down. Slower bouncer outside off, gets very big on Jacks as he goes for a flat-batted smash and he slices it high over extra cover. Stubbs backpedals from mid-off but it falls well behind him. Maybe he could've tried to run back rather than backpedaling which would've allowed him to cover a greater distance
Khaleel Ahmed to Will Jacks, 1 run, good length outside off, slapped to sweeper cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Patidar cuts it to sweeper cover
Rasikh Dar Salam, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Rasikh Salam to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, dropped again. Fourth chance goes down in a matter of two overs. Fuller than a length outside off, Patidar looks to drive on the up but is through the shot early, hitting it in the air to the left of cover. Very difficult chance for Axar who flies across, getting both hands to it. But he fails to hold on. Would've been a screamer
Rasikh Salam to Will Jacks, 1 run, driven hard to long-on
Rasikh Salam to Rajat Patidar, no run, back of a length outside off, slower one, Patidar cuts gently to cover
Rasikh Salam to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, low full toss on middle, Patidar whips it to deep midwicket
Rasikh Salam to Will Jacks, no run, back of a length outside off, slower one, Jacks lets it go thinking it could be a wide. But it's inside the marker
Rasikh Salam to Will Jacks, wide, left alone again and this one is definitely a wide outside off
Rasikh Salam to Will Jacks, FOUR, high full toss on off, and Jacks swipes it away past short fine leg. Goes racing to the boundary
Khaleel Ahmed to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, full ball outside off, slower one, Patidar gets forward and drives to deep point. Another fifty for Patidar - his fifth in the last seven innings
Khaleel Ahmed to Will Jacks, no run, length ball across off, Jacks looks to slog but it's an off-cutter that grips and turns past the edge
Khaleel Ahmed to Will Jacks, no run, beaten by the off-cutter again! Length ball across off, he looks to drive but it goes past the edge
Khaleel Ahmed to Will Jacks, no run, full outside off, Jacks again looks to slog but gets a thick under-edge that goes rolling to the keeper. Again got deceived by the slower one
Khaleel Ahmed to Will Jacks, 1 run, 131.8kph length ball outside off, Jacks goes after it and slaps it on the bounce to deep point
Khaleel Ahmed to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, good length outside off, Patidar looks to slap it away but mistimes it to long-off
Good couple of overs for DC.
Rasikh Salam to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, pitched up outside off, Patidar drills it to long-off
Rasikh Salam to Will Jacks, 1 run, slower one floated up outside off, Jacks reaches out and slaps it to long-off
Rasikh Salam to Rajat Patidar, wide, very wide outside off, left alone
Rasikh Salam to Rajat Patidar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rasikh Salam to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Axar!! Finally DC hang onto one. Short of length just outside off, Patidar tries slapping it away but is late on it and miscues it to the right of Axar at extra cover. It's not a straightforward chance. He has to move across quickly before diving with both hands, and he grabs it nicely. Rajat Patidar c Axar b Rasikh Salam 52(32) [4s-3 6s-3]
Cameron Green, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rasikh Salam to Green, 1 run, slower one floated up on off, Green flicks it through midwicket

Rasikh Salam to Will Jacks, FOUR, full and wide, Jacks drives powerfully through cover and it goes quickly to the right of sweeper cover. Mukesh runs across and tries to stop it with his foot but fails. Ordinary effort from him

Rasikh Salam to Will Jacks, 2 runs, miscued in the air but falls wide of long-off! Back of the hand slower ball, kicks up off a length and Jacks gets it high on the bat as he looks to slog. Good work in the deep to save the boundary
Axar Patel [2.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Axar to Green, no run, tossed up full outside off, Green presses forward to drive and gets beaten
Axar to Green, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, Green presses back and punches it down the ground to long-off
Axar to Will Jacks, no run, flatter delivery just outside off, Will Jacks presses back and slaps it straight to extra cover
Axar to Will Jacks, no run, length delivery on middle, Will Jacks looks to heave it away and misses, just goes over off-stump
Axar to Will Jacks, 1 run, flatter delivery outside off, Will Jacks reaches out and slaps it over extra cover, long-off gets around and takes it on the bounce
Axar to Green, 1 run, to point, length delivery on off-stump, punched towards point for one, another tight over from DC
Kuldeep Yadav [2.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
Kuldeep Yadav to Green, 2 runs, full on leg-stump, worked away to deep mid-wicket, they shuffle back for two
Kuldeep Yadav to Green, no run, flatter delivery outside off, skids through and Green mistimes a cut back towards the bowler off the bottom half
Kuldeep Yadav to Green, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, punched down the ground to long-off
Kuldeep Yadav to Will Jacks, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Will Jacks, out Caught by Axar!! Straight to the man! Both set batters are suddenly gone! Length delivery outside off, Will Jacks presses back and makes a bit of room before slapping it straight to Axar at cover. No mistake from the skipper, the Capitals are getting rewarded for bowling tight. Will Jacks c Axar b Kuldeep Yadav 41(29) [4s-3 6s-2]
Mahipal Lomror, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Yadav to Lomror, 1 run, tossed up full on off-stump, pushed down the ground to long on
Kuldeep Yadav to Green, no run, tossed up full on off-stump, skids through and beats the outside edge as Green presses forward to defend

Highlights (Overs 7-15) - Kuldeep goes for 15 in the first over after the powerplay - Axar drops Will Jacks on 19 - Hope drops Patidar on 42 - Both those chances came in the span of 3 balls off Kuldeep - Stubbs drops a slightly tough chance off Khaleel (Jacks on 24) - Axar drops Patidar on 46 (off Rasikh Dar) - A 29-ball fifty for Patidar, 5th in his last 7 innings - DC pull things back with wickets of Patidar and Jacks
Ishant Sharma [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Ishant to Lomror, 2 runs, good length delivery on middle, Lomror hangs back and eases it down towards deep backward point, they shuffle back for two

Ishant to Lomror, 1 run, length delivery slanting across outside off, Lomror throws his hands at it and gets a thick outside edge, it flies away towards third man and the fielder takes it on the bounce
Ishant to Green, 1 run, full on off-stump, Green prods forward and knocks it to mid-off, he takes the fielder on for a tight single
Ishant to Lomror, wide, banged in short, ends up high and down leg, probably wide on both counts
Ishant to Lomror, wide, full and down leg, will be another wide
Ishant to Lomror, 1 run, length delivery wide outside off, Lomror reaches out and cuts it away to deep point
Rajat Patidar in middle overs (7-15) in IPL 2024 Runs: 255 Balls: 136 Dismissals: 9 Avg: 28.33 SR: 187.5 4s/6s: 6/26 The only other batter with 20 (or more) sixes in this phase is Riyan Parag (20).
Ishant to Green, 1 run, low full-toss on off-stump, driven down the ground to long-on
Ishant to Lomror, 1 run, length delivery wide outside off, cut away fiercely towards sweeper cover, the fielder nearly over-ran that but did well to stop it

Timeout. The slowdown has been considerable for RCB. The wicket has seemingly started to hold up just a bit and with both set batters gone, scoring seems to have gotten tough. Credit to DC for pulling things back so strongly
Most sixes against spin this season 20 - Rajat Patidar 20 - Abhishek Sharma 17 - Heinrich Klaasen
Kuldeep Yadav to Lomror, 1 run, tossed up full on off-stump, smacked hard down towards long-off but can't get it straight enough to beat the man
Twenty balls since the last boundary now

Kuldeep Yadav to Green, SIX, and there it is right on cue! Floated up full and just outside off, just a touch too full, Green pressed forward and got right under it before lofting it clean over long-off
Kuldeep Yadav to Green, SIX, two in a row! RCB needed these! Dragged down short, over-corrected and Green was waiting for it, he pressed back and heaved it away over deep mid-wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Green, 2 runs, length delivery on middle, worked away to deep mid-wicket, they scurry back for two
Kuldeep Yadav to Green, leg byes, 1 run, full and down leg, was the googly, Green was looking to use the pace and paddle it fine, got a top-edge that went towards short third man

Kuldeep Yadav to Lomror, SIX, third six of the over! This is the big over RCB were so desperately after. Floated up full on middle, Lomror leant in, got a good stride forward and slog-swept it over the deep mid-wicket ropes
Khaleel Ahmed [3.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Green, no run, length delivery slanting across outside off, Green looks to punch it away and misses

Khaleel Ahmed to Green, FOUR, flat and nearly goes all the way! Full and wide outside off, too much width and Green absolutely demolished this over extra cover, went flat and just bounced inside the ropes
Khaleel Ahmed to Green, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, slapped away to sweeper cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Lomror, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Lomror, out Caught by Abishek Porel!! Straight up in the air and gone! Full on middle, was pace off and it just stuck into the surface, Lomror had a big swipe across the line and it took the top-edge before going straight up in the air. Went high and over the keeper, he ran back, nearly made a meal of it but held on. Lomror c Abishek Porel b Khaleel Ahmed 13(8) [6s-1]
Dinesh Karthik, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Khaleel Ahmed to Karthik, no run, length delivery slanting across just outside off, Karthik looked to loft it over cover and missed
Khaleel Ahmed to Karthik, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Karthik, out Caught by Kuldeep Yadav!! Two wickets in the air and the crowd is stunned! DK is gone for a duck! Length delivery outside off, looked like it was pace off again and Karthik had to delay his shot a touch as he looked to cut, he hit it straight to the man at backward point. RCB losing momentum at the wrong time. Karthik c Kuldeep Yadav b Khaleel Ahmed 0(2)
Swapnil Singh comes in as the impact sub for RCB
Swapnil Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rasikh Dar Salam [2.0-0-18-1] is back into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Green, no run, slower delivery full and just outside off from round the wicket, Green loads up and has a big swipe before missing
Rasikh Salam to Green, 1 run, nails the yorker just outside off, right on the popping crease and not much Green can do, he jams it back into his pads and they scurry through for one
Rasikh Salam to Swapnil Singh, wide, full and wide outside off, just goes a touch too wide and will need to bowl that again
Rasikh Salam to Swapnil Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rasikh Salam to Swapnil Singh, out Caught by Kushagra!! Straight down the fielder's throat again! Slower length delivery on middle, Swapnil Singh hung back and heaved it away, hit it pretty well but picked the man out at deep backward square leg. RCB really losing their way now as a 7th wicket goes down. 200 looking that much further away with every ball. Swapnil Singh c Kushagra b Rasikh Salam 0(1)
Karn Sharma, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Rasikh Salam to Karn Sharma, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, bunted down the ground to long-on
Rasikh Salam to Green, 1 run, very full on off-stump, dug out towards cover for a quick single
Rasikh Salam to Karn Sharma, 1 run, fires it into the blockhole again, on leg-stump and Karn Sharma clips it out towards deep mid-wicket, only a single, another superb over for DC
Mukesh Kumar [2.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack

Mukesh Kumar to Karn Sharma, FOUR, that's a great strike! Length delivery wide outside off, not a great delivery as he didn't have protection behind square on the off-side, Karn Sharma just opened the face of the bat and scythed it up and over backward point, one-bounce four
Mukesh Kumar to Karn Sharma, byes, 1 run, slower length delivery just outside off, Karn Sharma swings and misses, they pinch a bye to the keeper
Long chat between skipper and bowler
Mukesh Kumar to Green, no run, brillaint bowling, nails the slower yorker just outside off, Green gets a thick inside edge that goes towards square leg, he refuses the single to retain strike
RCB review for wide, don't think they'll get this overturned

Mukesh Kumar to Green, no run, very well bowled again, saw Green running at him and pushed this very full and wide, kept it out of his reach as he looked to drill it away, Green not happy that wasn't called a wide
Mukesh Kumar to Green, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Mukesh Kumar to Green, out Karn Sharma Run Out!! 1 run completed. Low full-toss outside off, Green mistimes it down the ground to long-on, they charge back for two but it was never there, Karn Sharma sacrifices his wicket to keep Green on strike. This is excellent bowling from Mukesh. Karn Sharma run out (Shai Hope/Mukesh Kumar) 6(4) [4s-1]
Mohammed Siraj, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Green, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Mukesh Kumar to Green, out Siraj Run Out!! 2 runs completed. Very full and wide outside off, Green carved it away to deep point and they charged back for two, the throw came straight back to the bowler and Siraj didn't spot it, he was running for the third but was promptly run-out. Siraj run out (Abishek Porel/Mukesh Kumar) 0(0)

21:10 Local Time, 15:40 GMT, 21:10 IST: Excellent bowling from DC to restrict RCB to under 200 here. After winning the toss and opting to bowl, they picked up two wickets in the powerplay but couldn't keep the runs down. Faf went early and Kohli who was looking in full flow couldn't carry on. But Will Jacks and Rajat Patidar batted brilliantly in the early middle-overs. They took the bowling on and struck sixes at will. Patidar got to yet another fifty and RCB were looking set for another big 200+ total. RCB did have their fair share of luck as DC put down as many as four chances quite early. However, there was a major slowdown around the 12th over. DC's spinners suddenly found some bite off the deck and the track seemed to slow up. Both set batters were dismissed in quick succession and barring an unbeaten 32 from Green, no one else was able to make a significant contribution. Delhi bowled brillaintly at the death as well. Back shortly with the chase.
RCB innings progression \nOvers 1-10: 110/2 (RR: 11) \nOvers 11-20: 77/7 (RR: 7.7)
Most ducks in the IPL 18 - Dinesh Karthik 17 - Glenn Maxwell 17 - Rohit Sharma 16 - Piyush Chawla 16 - Sunil Narine

Patidar: Wicket was two-paced when I went in. Ball was holding, especially the slower ball. Have been smarter in selecting which bowlers to go after in the last few games. I try my best to read it from the hand. This target is defendable. Can defend easily if we bowl in good areas.
Out come the players and umpires for the chase. RCB will need to bowl really well to defend this. David Warner comes in as the impact sub for DC and he's opening the innings with JFM.
